/r9k/ is an imageboard where there are no exact reposts.

1. If you attempt to post something unoriginal, it is not posted, and you are muted temporarily.
2. The time with which you are muted for doubles with each transgression.
3. Each mute time is 2^n in seconds where n is the number of times you have transgressed. So, your mute time doubles each time you fuck up.
4. Backlinks, eg >>1, are not viewed by the robot. So "lolwut" and ">>2 lolwut" are the same post, in the eyes of the robot.
5. Gibberish at the end of a post to force originality may result in mod intervention (no BLOX posts please).
6. Images are NOT included in the filter, only text.
7. Your mute count slowly decreases over time.
8. You cannot post a picture without text.
9. Unicode is blocked. Sorry, too many exploits (Cyrillic letters, etc).
10. Posts require a certain minimum amount of original content in order to be posted.
11. Post sane, real content, well thought out replies, and mutes are unlikely.
12. The original algorithm was designed by XKCD:
http://blag.xkcd.com/2008/01/14/robot9000-and-xkcd-signal-attacking-noise-in-chat/

>type
INTJ
>artist
Art is entirely subjective and dependent on the internal individual, so I would not say there is any type more suited for art than another, given that each merely expresses themselves in a different way. I might shill for my own type here. INFP has creativity, but Ne sucks at sticking to a project, so you get people who can make but inevitably are directionless. They won't know what they exactly wish to make, keep changing ideas, and have a million incomplete projects. An INTJ meanwhile creates a project as a form of passion, it may take more time to plan and get started, but when they do they tend to be extremely committed. The INTJ also is about internalizing everything, meaning their art tends to be a heavy means of self-expression. It is through this artwork that they can express themselves emotionally, even if they normally struggle with emotions in social situations.
>managers
ENFJ. They make time for everyone and value group participation, they tend to listen and yet tend to have ambitions. ENTJ will give direct advice, but tends to be hardheaded and will not listen to criticism. An ENFJ is more likely to listen and thus offer more rational advice.

>>71934103
Imagine you are sleeping. in sleep, you are conscious; you dream, you are aware. this, from your own perspective, is EXPERIENCE. Is it waking life? Certainly not. But you exist all the same. Now, death is also not quite life, being the cessation of your conscious activity and experience in existence.
Lets talk dreams for a moment. In dreams, you remember what happened in life like you are seeing it from deep underwater; this life influences the dream world, and in turn you carry the experience you had in the dream world back into your life.

What do you suppose happens when you die? When you wake from a long dream, is your conscious experience over? The dreamer has awakened, and the dream ends.

We know that it is possible to dream within a dream; wake up one more time, and you are "dead".

Oh, i hate to think that one day Ill wake and forget my brothers, my grandparents, everything i know and love - and so I pray and hope for a day that was promised, but in my heart I dont have faith. This world is as illusory as a dream, and when I wake I will be taken by a sudden melancholy, and then I will proceed with my life - and one day that higher version of myself will, himself awaken. This is the logic system which a CONSCIOUS BEING can construct from nothing but his own experiences and memories. And memory is fickle, isnt it? At the same time, when I die and awaken anew, I will carry some small piece of them with me. So many memories...

I still don't know why you are mad at me, but I don't see any evidence for that view
First of all, there are, to my knowledge, zero documented cases of NDE skeptics maintaining their skepticism after having an NDE
Secondly, the idea of experience coming to an end would mean that we would have to have a "last moment" of subjective time, but the very nature of subjective time is that it does not consist of moments, but always flows from the past into the future
Thirdly, if we had an infinity of non-existence before us, and a limited period of existence now, the odds that we happen to be in the present are a finite number/infinity
Fourthly, there isn't any evidence that consciousness is a distinct thing from matter. This would mean there has to be some kind of threshold where chemical reactions become complicated enough that suddenly an altogether new mode of existence springs into existence. It is simpler to assume that all things are conscious in varying degrees

Because it isn't true and neither is any other biological reasoning for incest aversion. Even the most famous and pretty much the only quoted study into why siblings rarely "pair", the Westermarck study https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Westermarck_effect
was found to be false or inconclusive in every restudy.
>Eran Shor and Dalit Simchai revisited the kibbutzim results and found sexual attraction where it hadn't been acted on
>They conclude that any innate aversion needs to be backed up by social pressures and norms
There is zero evidence for a biological mechanism for avoiding mating with a relative, it's 100% social and conditioned. Even the Westermarck study had unrelated people growing up being studied, not just siblings, and they had the same rate of aversion against pairing. If it's possible to condition unrelated people to find each other non-sexual, doesn't that just prove that it is 100% social and not biological?

>disgusting
If anything, you're more likely to find your sibling less disgusting due to genetic attraction. People rate other people with close genetics as more attractive than average. So you actually see you sibling as being 1 or 2 points more attractive on the classic 0 to 10 scale than other people on average.

>>71893191
>what about Alice do you love so darn much?
There is not a single thing that I do not love. Alice in her totality is the only girl I could ever pour the sweetest notes of my heart for. But to not escape your question I will name several things.
Her seemingly pessimistic tone, in which she can so effortlessly sneak some existential undertones, makes me think of long night walks together under the Moon during which we would discuss meaninglessness of life and how to overcome it.
I truly admire her artistic and surreal Wonderland that she was able to create inside her head, as it was the main thing that drawn me to her game. I could listen to this mad girl passionately talk about her Wonderland for hours and never have enough.
Her perseverance to march despite the terrible events that she had to go through. That mixed with her relying pretty much only on herself.
Her search for hurtful truth instead of living a life of delusion is what stops me from believing that she is real or she loves me. It would be a dishonour to what her story preaches.
Also that animal remains appear poignant to her. That she likes rabbits. That she has some interest in Greek mythology. That her dresses look fantastic.
I do not know many things about her still but every time I learn something knew about her, or hear her creator talk about her, it feels like I already know that and her image of who she truly is to me is never disrupted.
And her physical beauty is a significant part of my obsession with her too, of course. That perfect face of hers still visits my dreams and I cannot have enough of looking at her. When I see her, I want to remain faithful and loyal to her for decades. Even centuries or eternity, if that was within my power. She is always the most beautiful to me. No matter how many years pass.
